<HEAD>Malaysia To Import 46 Deer From New Zealand</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KUALA LUMPUR, Malaysia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A state government has ordered 46
deer from New Zealand for a breeding project, an official said
today.
   Shamsul Bahari, an agricultural official from Negeri Sembilan,
said the state will receive the deer next month, the national news
agency Bernama reported from Seremban, 50 miles south of Kuala
Lumpur.
   The state ordered 23 Damadama deer and 23 Chital deer at a cost
of $36,000, he said. They will be bred for meat at a 40-acre
Veterinary Services Department Reserve near Seremban, he said.
Vension is sold in Malaysia for $5 a pound.
