<1ST_LINE>u i AM-Japan-Markets     04-26 0168</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Japan-Markets,0172</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Stocks Close At Record High, Dollar Weakens</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Tokyo stock market closed at a record high
Tuesday while the U.S. dollar weakened.
   In the Tokyo Stock Exchange, the 225-issue Nikkei Stock Average
closed at 27,246.77, 33.32 points higher than on Monday. The
market's main barometer briefly reached the all time high of
27,339.14 shortly after Tuesday's opening, but profit-taking
thwarted the early morning rally, traders said.
   Meanwhile, the dollar closed at 124.57 yen, 0.43 yen lower than
Monday's close of 125. It opened at 124.65 yen and traded in a
narrow range of 124.55 yen to 124.70 yen, traders said.
   Analysts said initial bullish sentiment in the stock market
following the record close on Monday pushed stock prices up in
early trading, but the trend slowly reversed, fueled by
profit-taking.
   ``The market started out on a bullish note, but then ran out of
gas and started moving down,'' said a trader at a major securities
firm, who asked not to be identified.
</TEXT>
