<1ST_LINE>r a PM-HeartAttack-Bus     04-26 0330</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Heart Attack-Bus,0341</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Driver Dies; Three Boys Avert Crash</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By PAT MILTON</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>CENTRAL ISLIP, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A school bus went careening out of
control after the driver suffered a fatal heart attack, but three
junior high school boys brought it to a halt after seeing the
driver topple from her seat.
   ``They are heroes,'' said Jack Cassidy, principal at Ralph Reed
Junior High School in Central Islip, Long Island.
   The full-size bus was carrying five youngsters to the school
Monday morning, threading through traffic on busy Route 111 at 15
mph, authorities said. It narrowly missed a car and a utility pole
when it veered left into oncoming traffic after the driver's heart
attack.
   ``We heard something fall. I looked out the window and saw the
bus heading for a car. I didn't know what happened,'' said Jack
Florival, 14, one of the boys who took over when driver Mary
Flammer, 48, of Holbrook, toppled from her seat.
   Florival and two 15-year-olds, Sean Mohan and Nigel Boyer, ran
forward from their seats in the rear.
   ``I grabbed the wheel,'' said Florival, ``Sean and Nigel slammed
on the brakes.''
   The bus mounted the curb and came to rest on the sidewalk in
front of a house. They boys went to the house for help but got no
response.
   ``We heard somebody inside but they wouldn't come to the door,''
said Florival. ``Then another school bus driver stopped and he
called police.''
   An ambulance took Flammer to a hospital where she was pronounced
dead, said police spokesman John Hayden.
   The driver had passed her last physical March 11, said Philip
DiDomenico, spokesman for her employer, the Suffolk Transportation
Co.
   Cassidy, told the youngsters he was going to write to President
Reagan, Gov. Mario Cuomo and the school board about their actions.
   Florival said his uncle had taught him to drive ``a little'' in
case of an emergency.
   ``I was frightened,'' he said, ``but God was with us.''
</TEXT>
