<1ST_LINE>r i PM-BRF--YugoslavQuake     04-26 0127</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Yugoslav Quake,0128</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Earthquake Shakes Yugoslavia; No Injuries Reported</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BELGRADE, Yugoslavia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A strong earthquake today shook the
central region of the Adriatic Sea, the state news agency Tanjug
said. The quake was felt along the entire Adriatic coast, but no
damage or injuries were reported.
   The temblor struck shortly after midnight and measured 5.4 on
the Richter scale, according to the Yugoslav Federal Seismological
Institute.
   Tanjug said the epicenter of the quake was located near the
island of Palagruza in the middle of the Adriatic Sea off the
Hercegovina coast.
   The Richter scale is a guage of the energy released by an
earthquake, as measured by the ground motion recorded on a
seismograph. A quake measuring 5 on the scale can cause
considerable damage.
</TEXT>
