<1ST_LINE>d a PM-BRF--Obit-Franklin     04-26 0163</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Obit-Franklin,0169</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Composer, Singer Carolyn Franklin Dies at Home of Sister Aretha</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BLOOMFIELD HILLS, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Songwriter and singer Carolyn Ann
Franklin, 43-year-old sister of singer Aretha Franklin, has died of
cancer at her sister's home.
   Among Miss Franklin's compositions were ``Gotta Find Me An
Angel'' and ``Ain't No Way,'' both made into million-sellers by
Aretha Franklin.
   She also arranged ``Take Another Little Piece of My Heart'' by
Erma Franklin, another sister and singer, a song later made popular
by Janis Joplin.
   Carolyn Franklin was born in Memphis and moved with her family
to Buffalo, N.Y., and then to Detroit in 1946. As a child, she
formed a singing group with members of the young people's choir at
New Bethel Baptist Church, where her father was pastor.
   She, Erma and their cousin, Brenda Bryant, sang background on
Aretha Franklin's early records.
   Besides her sisters, survivors include her grandmother and two
brothers.
   Funeral arrangements were pending for Miss Franklin, who died
Monday.
</TEXT>
