<HEAD>Bomb Injures Three In West Beirut</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIRUT, Lebanon (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A small bomb exploded today near a fruit
juice shop in Moslem west Beirut, and police said three people were
injured.
   A police spokesman said the bomb, planted in a garbage bin, went
off at 2:30 p.m. near the juice shop in the crowded Barbir Street.
   ``The explosion shattered the shop's glass front and three
pedestrians were slightly injured by glass shards,'' said the
spokesman, who cannot be named because of regulations.
   The explosion also damaged two parked cars, the police spokesman
added.
   On Saturday, a pickup truck loaded with explosives went off in
the northern city of Tripoli, killing 70 people and wounding 110 in
the deadliest car bombing in Lebanon in three years.
