<2ND_LINE>PM-Germany-Defense,0137</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>New West German Defense Minister Named</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BONN, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Rupert Scholz, considered a strong
backer of NATO and closer ties with the United States, has been
appointed defense minister, Chancellor Helmut Kohl announced today.
   The 50-year-old Scholz, West Berlin's minister for justice and
federal affairs, will replace Manfred Woerner next month. Woerner
will take over as the Western military alliance's secretary general
on July 1.
   Some defense experts expressed misgivings about the appointment
of Scholz. He has been a member of Kohl's governing Christian
Democratic party only since 1983 and does not sit in parliament. A
lawyer by training, he has no specific experience in military
issues.
   However, Kohl brushed aside that criticism, saying Scholz ``has
a clear understanding of political priorities and is a highly
skilled administrator.''
 
</TEXT>
