<HEAD>JSU Student Killed By Fellow Student</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JACKSON, Miss. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An argument over a broken car windshield
ended in the fatal shooting of a Jackson State football player,
authorities said.
   Hinds County Coroner Robert Martin said an autopsy showed Lerome
Brown, 24, bled to death after he was shot in the chest Monday
outside the campus union.
