<HEAD>Bodies of Five Men Found In Trunk Of Parked Car</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN JUAN, Puerto Rico (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The bullet-riddled bodies of five
young men were found Tuesday in the trunk of a car parked at a
suburban San Juan housing project, police said.
   Each victim's hands and feet were tied and each had been shot
repeatedly, police said.
   The men apparently were slain elsewhere, put into car's trunk
and driven to the Sabana Bajo housing project in the suburb of
Carolina, police spokesman Tony Santiago said.
   The bodies were taken to the Forensic Sciences Institute at the
Medical Center in Rio Piedras for examination. Institute director
Pio Rechani said all were between the age of 18 and 23.
   One of the victims was identified as Luis Alberto Diaz Orta, 20,
of the Ramon T. Colon Housing Project in Carolina. The identities
of the others were not known.
