<HEAD>DeMocker Named to DOT Public Affairs Post</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Reagan plans to nominate Wendy
Monson DeMocker, a government press secretary and former aide to
Sen. David Durenberger, R-Minn., as an assistant secretary of
transportation, the White House announced Tuesday.
   Mrs. DeMocker, 30, would succeed Dale A. Petroskey as assistant
secretary for public affairs if confirmed by the Senate.
