<HEAD>Grain, Soybean Futures Open Lower</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Grain and soybean futures prices opened slightly
lower today on the Chicago Board of Trade.
   Follow-through selling from Monday's lower close provided some
initial weakness across the board, and forecasts for rain in the
nation's midsection during the week ahead kept prices on the
defensive in early trading, analysts said.
   In early trading, wheat was { cent to 1\ cents lower with the
contract for delivery in May at $3.10} a bushel; corn was unchanged
to } cent lower with May at $1.99\ a bushel; oats were { cent to 1}
cents lower with May at $1.63\ a bushel; soybeans were \ cent to 2{
cents lower with May at $6.58\ a bushel.
   Livestock and meat futures were mixed in early trading on the
Chicago Mercantile Exchange.
