<1ST_LINE>r f BC-Rowntree-Nestle     04-26 0178</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Rowntree-Nestle,0187</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Rowntree Rejects Nestle Takeover Offer As Unwelcome</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   British confectioner Rowntree PLC on Tuesday
rejected as ``unwelcome'' and inadequate a 2.1 billion-pound, or
$3.95 billion, takeover bid from Swiss coffee and chocolate giant
Nestle S.A.
   The $16.73-a-share price exceeds the $11.84 recently paid by
Jacobs Suchard S.A., another Swiss coffee and chocolate company,
when it increased its stake in Rowntree to 14.9 percent and said it
was seeking a 25-percent holding.
   Jacobs Suchard said it wouldn't launch a full bid for at least a
year unless another bidder emerged.
   Nestle said it already has acquired about 6.6 percent of
Rowntree's shares.
   But Rowntree recommended to its shareholders that they take no
action in regard to Nestle's offer, which it said it intends to
resist firmly.
   ``The (Rowntree) board have already stated and continue to
believe that the business of Rowntree can best be developed ... as
an independent group,'' Rowntree said in a statement.
   ``The offer from Nestle is unwelcome and does not reflect the
value of Rowntree's unique collection of international brands.''
</TEXT>
